# Superannuation Contribution Holidays Indicator

## identifier
de5581

## type
boolean

## definition
Was the reporting party on a contribution holiday at a time during the relevant period?

A contribution holiday occurs when the sponsor of the fund ceases to make contributions to the fund.

## guidance
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values.

TRUE = The reporting party was on a contribution holiday at a time during the relevant period.
FALSE = The reporting party was not on a contribution holiday at any time during the relevant period

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=SuperannuationContribution.Holidays.Indicator
- classification=em/emsup/emsup.02.02
- period=duration
